{
  "texts": [
    "Quantitative N/I N/I Wu and Zhang, 2022 Hunan The study aims to develop a remote human-computer interaction and STEM teacher online training platform based on the embedded Internet of Things.",
    "It also sought to assess the effectiveness of this platform in addressing shortcomings identified in existing online teacher training platforms, particularly in areas such as information aggregation, resource construction, content setting, presentation, and learning support services.",
    "The study concluded that the STEM teacher online training system had clarified STEM curriculum design steps, standardized STEM design methods, enhanced cooperative learning abilities, and cultivated design thinking among the participants.",
    "Qualitative 38 Ten weeks Zeng et al., 2019 Guangdong To address the serious shortage of STEAM teachers in China by proposing strategies for improving the interdisciplinary knowledge and skills of STEAM teachers.",
    "The study aims to extend the pre-service training period, provide comprehensive training for inservice teachers, and improve the overall quality of teachers, especially those transitioning to STEAM roles."
  ]
}